OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781161488
OL,3,CBoys' reading remains in crisis as
OL,4,Cgender gap widens, report shows
OL,6,FA National Literacy Trust survey of
OL,7,Fmore than 125,000 children found fewer
OL,8,Fthan three in ten boys aged eight to
OL,9,F18 now say they enjoy reading in their
OL,10,Ffree time, compared with more than
OL,11,Ffour in ten girls.
OL,13,FAlthough children's enjoyment of
OL,14,Freading has risen for the first time
OL,15,Fin five years, the charity says levels
OL,16,Fremain significantly below those seen
OL,17,Fa decade ago. The rise is almost
OL,18,Fexclusively due to an improvement in
OL,19,Fthe responses of girls.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
