OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781161488
OL,3,CBoys' reading remains in crisis as
OL,4,Cgender gap widens, report shows
OL,6,FSpeaking to ITV News, Horowitz said:
OL,7,F"There is a war going on at the moment
OL,8,Fbetween books and other interests, in
OL,9,Fparticular smartphones and social
OL,10,Fmedia.
OL,12,F"Social media is in many ways the
OL,13,Fenemy of children, whereas books are
OL,14,Fthe friend.
OL,16,F"That is why fiction, and fiction for
OL,17,Fboys as much as for girls, matters now
OL,18,Fmore than ever because it slows things
OL,19,Fdown, it puts you in control.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781161488
OL,3,CBoys' reading remains in crisis as
OL,4,Cgender gap widens, report shows
OL,6,F"There's no algorithm guiding you when
OL,7,Fyou read a book. It is just you and
OL,8,Fthe author, with you having the choice
OL,9,Fof how fast you go, how much you read,
OL,10,Fwhat you read, whether you decide to
OL,11,Fcontinue reading. It gives you
OL,12,Fcontrol."
OL,14,FAt Dowlais Primary School in Merthyr
OL,15,FTydfil, the children we met showed the
OL,16,Fcomplexity behind the figures: they
OL,17,Fall enjoyed reading but described the
OL,18,Fdaily battle between books and screens.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
