OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781161488
OL,3,CBoys' reading remains in crisis as
OL,4,Cgender gap widens, report shows
OL,6,FResearchers are unsure why boys often
OL,7,Freport lower levels of reading
OL,8,Fenjoyment, but studies have discussed
OL,9,Fa range of possibilities. These
OL,10,Finclude boys being less likely to see
OL,11,Fthemselves as readers, differences in
OL,12,Fthe types of books they choose, and
OL,13,Feven that they may be more susceptible
OL,14,Fto becoming addicted to the type of
OL,15,Falgorithms used by social media
OL,16,Fplatforms.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
