PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781161488
OL,3,CBoys' reading remains in crisis as
OL,4,Cgender gap widens, report shows
OL,6,FHorowitz said children need the
OL,7,Ffreedom to discover the type of
OL,8,Freading that excites them - whether
OL,9,Fthat is a novel, comic, newspaper or
OL,10,Fsomething else entirely.
OL,12,F"Reading is a muscle," he said. "It
OL,13,Fneeds to get started with whatever
OL,14,Fcomes your way, whether it is the
OL,15,FBeano, or Tintin, or a newspaper, or
OL,16,Fanything.
OL,26,@tD@AOUtD@VO]tD@aOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30612
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781161488
OL,3,CBoys' reading remains in crisis as
OL,4,Cgender gap widens, report shows
OL,6,F"If you are given the encouragement
OL,7,Fand you have the right environment and
OL,8,Fthe reading muscle has begun to work,
OL,9,Fthere is no saying where it can take
OL,10,Fyou."
OL,12,FFor Horowitz, reading is not simply
OL,13,Fentertainment - it is a vital skill
OL,14,Fthat needs to be continually exercised.
OL,16,F"People talk about reading as being a
OL,17,Fleisure activity. It is not. Your
OL,18,Fbrain is working overtime," he said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@EO]xD@AOUzD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30613
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1781161488
OL,3,CBoys' reading remains in crisis as
OL,4,Cgender gap widens, report shows
OL,6,F"You are actually imagining entire
OL,7,Fworlds. You are filling those worlds
OL,8,Fwith people. You are meeting those
OL,9,Fpeople, understanding them."
OL,11,FThe author emphasised that parents had
OL,12,Fa crucial role in making reading part
OL,13,Fof family life.
OL,15,F"Children won't share their social
OL,16,Fmedia or their computer games with
OL,17,Fyou, but they might share their
OL,18,Fstories with you."
OL,20,FBack in Merthyr Tydfil, the children
OL,21,Fhad a similar message.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@\O]wD@AOUzD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
